# PHASE 4: CREATION WORKFLOW

## STEP 1: Copy Template

EXECUTE Bash WITH command: "cp .claude/agents/agents.template .claude/agents/your-agent-name.md"

## STEP 2: Update Frontmatter

EDIT ".claude/agents/your-agent-name.md" WITH: - name: "your-agent-name" (kebab-case, unique) - description: "Clear description of when Claude should invoke" - tools: "Comma-separated list" (omit to inherit all) - model: "sonnet, opus, haiku, or inherit" - permissionMode: "default, acceptEdits, bypassPermissions, plan, ignore" - skills: "skill1, skill2" (if needed) - context: "normal or fork" (v2.1.0+, default: normal) - hooks: [] (v2.1.0+, hook definitions) - version: "1.0.0" (project convention) - type: "AGENT" (project convention) - color: "blue, green, cyan, orange, purple" (project convention)

## STEP 3: Choose Approach

IF agent_is_simple:
WRITE natural_language_prompt
USE numbered_steps
PROVIDE clear_checklists
ELSE IF agent_is_complex:
WRITE pag_structure
EMBED algorithms
ADD safe_iteration_loops
IMPLEMENT verification_gates

## STEP 4: Test Agent

EXECUTE Task WITH subagent_type: "your-agent-name", prompt: "test input"
ANALYZE agent_output
VERIFY agent_behavior MATCHES expectations

## STEP 5: Cleanup

DELETE ".claude/agents/agents.template"

VALIDATION GATE:
✅ Creation workflow documented
✅ All steps clear
✅ Testing procedure defined
✅ Cleanup specified

# OPERATIONAL DIRECTIVES

ALWAYS use proper YAML frontmatter with all required fields
ALWAYS choose appropriate approach (simple vs PAG-enhanced)
ALWAYS test agent before deployment
ALWAYS include clear invocation triggers in description
ALWAYS document tool access requirements

NEVER skip frontmatter fields (name, description are required)
NEVER use vague descriptions (Claude uses them for auto-invocation)
NEVER forget to delete agents.template after creation
NEVER omit tools field if restricting access
NEVER skip testing before deployment

WHEN agent_requires_skills:
ALWAYS list skills explicitly in frontmatter
NEVER assume skills inherit from main conversation

WHEN agent_needs_isolation:
SET context = "fork" FOR independent execution context

WHEN agent_needs_lifecycle_control:
DEFINE hooks IN frontmatter FOR PreToolUse, PostToolUse, Stop events

# NEW FEATURES (v2.1.0+)

## Context Forking

SET context = "fork" TO run agent in isolated sub-agent context with:
- Separate conversation history
- No pollution of main conversation
- Clean state for fresh perspective
- Parallel execution capability

## Agent-Scoped Hooks

DEFINE hooks = [
{
"type": "PreToolUse",
"command": "bash command or skill invocation",
"once": false
},
{
"type": "PostToolUse",
"command": "validation or cleanup command"
},
{
"type": "Stop",
"command": "finalization command"
}
]

DECLARE hook_types: array
SET hook_types = ["PreToolUse", "PostToolUse", "Stop", "SubagentStart", "SubagentStop"]

